rComments: Incredibly awkward. Vague knowledge of course material. No flow between topics. Test and lecture are completely unrelated. The effort I put into the class was not representative of my grade.

Dr. Kaupp is an extremely helpful professor if you give her the chance.  Although she does not have the most structured lectures, she is intelligent and gives out solid information. Attendance in class and section is recommended, but not required. Tests are all multiple choice.  Get your APA formatting down,it is vital for the final paper.

Dr. Kaupp is not the most confident public speaker the first few class meetings. However once she gets to know who is paying attention she gets much better. She is very intelligent and is happy to answer questions. She requires a draft and final paper, pay attention to your APA format.

Although she was unorganized while lecturing, her structure through power point notes were very beneficial. she was willing to meet outside of class, even off campus and gave me extra books to look at. over the quarter, it seemed like her confidence as a lecturer grew as she became more comfortable with our scrutiny.
Two 50-multiple question exam with a studyguide that helps you only a little, 2 page- and 10 page essay, boring powerpoint based class.I will never take her class again.

Look, listen to me. There are so many professors well worth the money you're paying (or the government is paying). Put it to good use and go to them and stay away from Kaupp. You will walk out of this course with little to nothing. Stay away! Horrible professor.

She pauses, yes, and discussions float around sometimes, yes, but most of it is student-led. She responds to the students that tune in to her. The kids in the back just don't know what's goin on as much. She still keeps the class going through the material and we had an AWESOME guest speaker that demonstrated some Wilhelm Reich and other stuff. fun
Jenny was my field studies supervisor and was very flexible and understanding.  She facilitated a positive group experience.
If you can avoid her, do it. She is a ready nice lady and tries to help, but just confuses you more. She babbles in lecture and trails off and then laughs.  YOU HAVE NO IDEA WHATS GOING ON!!!

Very kind with a great sense of humor.  The one thing this professor lacks is self confidence!  She lectures straight from her own notes and is always afraid that she will bore the class.  She would be an excellent teacher if she was confident and expressed interest in the course material.  Good powerpoint.  Good assignments.  Great lady-hillarious

Jenny is a kind person, but isn't too effective as a lecturer. She tends to be rather unorganized and the topics are not the most interesting. However, she is very helpful in office hours. Overall, she's a psychotherapist with a psychoanalytic orientation, so her psycholigcal views are not the most popular; so I presume.

Dr. Kaupp knows her stuff, but isn't very good at lecturing - she seems to get extremely nervous and will pause for long periods of time while she gathers her thoughts. It was very hard for me to pay attention. She had good intentions, but I was not very impressed.
Her lectures are boring, and she isn't very good at it.  She is very helpful and kind. She is a pretty new professor, so I think she is still getting used to it.
Good teacher but can be a little unorganized. Very nice though and will help if you need it.
